Sentencas: Silver-modified Ag/Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (Ag/BSCF) electrodes were prepared using an electroless deposition technique.
Titulo: Effect of a reducing agent for silver on the electrochemical activity of an Ag/Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ electrode prepared by electroless deposition technique

Sentencas: The morphology, microstructure and oxygen reduction reaction activity of the resulted Ag/BSCF electrodes were comparatively studied using Fourier transform infrared spectra, environmental scanning electron microscopy.
Titulo: Effect of a reducing agent for silver on the electrochemical activity of an Ag/Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ electrode prepared by electroless deposition technique

Sentencas: temperature-programmed oxygen desorption, X-ray diffraction, and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Effect of a reducing agent for silver on the electrochemical activity of an Ag/Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ electrode prepared by electroless deposition technique

Sentencas: An area-specific resistance as low as 0.038 Omega cm(2) was achieved for N2H4-reduced Ag/BSCF cathode at 600 degrees C. Carbonates were detected over the BSCF surface during the reduction of silver, which deteriorated both the charge-transfer process and diffusion process of HCHO-reduced Ag/BSCF cathode for the oxygen electrochemical reduction reaction.
Titulo: Effect of a reducing agent for silver on the electrochemical activity of an Ag/Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ electrode prepared by electroless deposition technique

Sentencas: An anode-supported single cell with an N2H4-reduced Ag/BSCF cathode showed a peak power of 826 mW cm(-2) at 600 degrees C.
Titulo: Effect of a reducing agent for silver on the electrochemical activity of an Ag/Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ electrode prepared by electroless deposition technique

Sentencas: In comparison, only 672 mW cm(-2) was observed with the HCHO-reduced Ag/BSCF cathode.
